      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KING NANGAR (1) goes very well this course and distance starting eight times for three wins and three minors. Missed the frame latest (29.83) when fourth over 520m at this track in a OPEN. Rates on top and should go close. RAPIDO KUNA (6) copped a check in the run and finished a well held 5 lengths sixth (30.71) last time in a Grade 5 at this track over 520m. May be worth another try. PAGE ONE NEWS (2) turned in a plain run last time when sixth at this track over 520m behind Intimidation (30.08) in a OPEN. Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to her name from seven starts. Great chance to atone. NANGAR ONYX (3) is in the mix despite finishing out of the placings here last start.",
